                            <comment id="15083" author="hongchao.zhang" created="Thu, 26 May 2011 03:42:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the problems are as follows,&lt;br/&gt;
1, rundbench is a bash script, and &quot;/bin/sh&quot; is not identical to &quot;/bin/bash&quot; on all distros.&lt;br/&gt;
2, if &quot;MPI_USER&quot; isn&apos;t set, don&apos;t use &quot;su $MPI_USER&quot; in function &quot;mpi_run&quot; in functions.sh&lt;br/&gt;
3, in some kinds of Linux(say, Ubuntu),  truncate is a system command, then the directory containing our truncate tools (the test directory)&lt;br/&gt;
   should be appended to use our truncate explicitly&lt;br/&gt;
4, in obdfilter-survey, drops sh as the interpreter of OBDSURVEY, for the same reason of #1&lt;br/&gt;
5, add VERBOSE option in test-framework.sh&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
